lead_paragraph: California, still drying off from an unusually wet and snowy December, was bracing today for two more storms, which are expected to set off mud slides in canyons, flooding in low-lying areas and high waves along the coast. A warning by the National Weather Service advised residents to monitor radio and television for emergency notices, and a winter storm watch was issued for the Sierra Nevada tonight.

headline.main: California Is Preparing for Two New Storms
